TWO EASY RECIPES FOR A BLACK HOLE
Black holes distort space-time so strongly they can capture light!
If the Earth turned into a black hole, it could fit inside a marble!
Black holes forming at the center of dying, fast rotating, massive stars drive powerful jets, causing extreme supernovae and long gamma-ray bursts.
Some super massive black holes at the center of galaxies feed on nearby gas.
They create powerful jets and bright emissions visible from the furthest reaches of space.
Two black holes in a binary system radiate gravitational waves. This drives them together until they merge, which releases a gravitational signal we can measure!
Wait for a very (very) massive star to age and collapse under its own weight!
